abstract: HARRISBURG, Pa., Nov. 21 (UPI)--The doctor for a team in the Philadelphia Phillies' minor league system has been charged, along with two other men, with illegally obtaining amphetamines by using the names of Philadelphia players, the Pennsylvania Justice Department said today.

Mayor Koch said yesterday that it would be "a disaster" if the Federal Government adopted a proposal by advisers to President-elect Ronald Reagan that would bar Federal grants to cities with rent-control laws. He expressed confidence that the Government could be persuaded that New York City's rent laws were "reasonable."

abstract: WASHINGTON, Nov. 20 -- A group of advisers to President-elect Ronald Reagan have recommended unanimously that Federal grants be withheld from cities that have rent-control laws.
